p that in mind as I move forward with this configuration!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Meaningful renderer coverage for doxia-site-renderer 2.0.0 usually needs Maven/Doxia runtime pieces that are not pulled by the normal direct library dependency: maven-artifact is a provided dependency for the public skin API, and non-XHTML Doxia parser modules are test-scoped in the artifact POM because parser component descriptors must be present on the classpath.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven:maven-artifact:3.6.3\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"doxia-site-renderer exposes createContextForSkin(Artifact, ...) and upstream tests create skin artifacts with DefaultArtifact; maven-artifact is declared as provided, so Gradle consumer tests do not receive it transitively.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-module-apt:2.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Doxia 2.0 parser modules are no longer all in doxia-core; APT rendering requires the module component descriptor on the test classpath.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-module-xdoc:2.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"XDoc rendering requires the separate parser module component descriptor on the test classpath.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-module-fml:2.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"FML rendering requires the separate parser module component descriptor on the test classpath.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For renderer behavior, obtain SiteRenderer/DefaultSiteRenderer through the Plexus/Sisu container rather than plain new DefaultSiteRenderer(), because velocity, Doxia, parser module manager, and container fields are injected. For skin/template tests, create a temporary skin JAR containing META-INF/maven/site.vm and pass it through createContextForSkin. Update tests to the 2.0 API: RenderingContext and SkinResourceLoader are gone; use DocumentRenderingContext, SiteRenderingContext, SiteRendererSink, and the current Renderer/SiteRenderer methods.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The existing 1.9.1 tests use removed APIs, so a simple version bump will keep failing javac.\",\n    \"Parser-module dependencies are only needed if tests exercise real APT/XDoc/FML site rendering; a narrower test limited to XHTML5 or simple model/context APIs may compile without them but will provide weaker coverage.\",\n    \"Native-image verification may still expose resource/reflection requirements around Sisu, Velocity templates, or parser component descriptors.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0c8ef00275815ad2016a3fb364be9c81958dbf3c80a2d3e0b6\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3603, "output": 2058, "cacheRead": 33280, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 38941, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782559569812, "responseId": "resp_0c8ef00275815ad2016a3fb352436c8195904d464ab42ea65a"}}
